cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the automated synthesis of controllers for hybrid systems with stochastic dynamics, which is a problem in control theory and systems engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also uses SMT solvers and nonlinear differential equations, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the application of the technique to the problem of insulin regulation, which is a topic in biomedical engineering, suggesting that cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on synthesizing controllers for hybrid systems suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as well.
